ing|boolean Plugin slug if found, false otherwise." ilk="function" line="859" lineend="868" name="_get_plugin_data_from_name" returns="string" signature="string _get_plugin_data_from_name(string $name, string $data = 'slug')"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="859" name="name" /><variable citdl="string" default="'slug'" ilk="argument" line="859" name="data" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="861" name="values" /><variable line="861" name="plugin" /></scope><scope attributes="protected" doc="Determine if we're on the TGMPA Install page.&#10;&#10;We use $current_screen when it is available, and a slightly less ideal&#10;conditional when it isn't (like when displaying the plugin information&#10;thickbox).&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;&#10;@global object $current_screen&#10;@return boolean True when on the TGMPA page, false otherwise." ilk="function" line="882" lineend="894" name="is_tgmpa_page" returns="boolean" signature="boolean is_tgmpa_page()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="884" name="current_screen" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="886" name="_GET" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Delete dismissable nag option when theme is switched.&#10;&#10;This ensures that the user is again reminded via nag of required&#10;and/or recommended plugins if they re-activate the theme.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.1" ilk="function" line="904" lineend="908" name="update_dismiss" signature="update_dismiss()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Forces plugin activation if the parameter 'force_activation' is&#10;set to true.&#10;&#10;This allows theme authors to specify certain plugins that must be&#10;active at all times while using the current theme.&#10;&#10;Please take special care when using this parameter as it has the&#10;potential to be harmful if not used correctly. Setting this parameter&#10;to true will not allow the specified plugin to be deactivated unless&#10;the user switches themes.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0" ilk="function" line="924" lineend="940" name="force_activation" signature="force_activation()"><variable citdl="get_plugins()" line="929" name="installed_plugins" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="931" name="plugin" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Forces plugin deactivation if the parameter 'force_deactivation'&#10;is set to true.&#10;&#10;This allows theme authors to specify certain plugins that must be&#10;deactived upon switching from the current theme to another.&#10;&#10;Please take special care when using this parameter as it has the&#10;potential to be harmful if not used correctly.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0" ilk="function" line="954" lineend="965" name="force_deactivation" signature="force_deactivation()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="959" name="plugin" /></scope></scope><scope doc="Helper function to register a collection of required plugins.&#10;&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@api&#10;&#10;@param array $plugins An array of plugin arrays&#10;@param array $config Optional. An array of configuration values" ilk="function" line="983" lineend="991" name="tgmpa" signature="tgmpa(array $plugins, array $config = array())"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="983" name="plugins" /><variable citdl="array" default="array()" ilk="argument" line="983" name="config" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="985" name="plugin" /></scope><scope classrefs="WP_List_Table" doc="List table class for handling plugins.&#10;&#10;Extends the WP_List_Table class to provide a future-compatible&#10;way of listing out all required/recommended plugins.&#10;&#10;Gives users an interface similar to the Plugin Administration&#10;area with similar (albeit stripped down) capabilities.&#10;&#10;This class also allows for the bulk install of plugins.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;&#10;@package TGM-Plugin-Activation&#10;@author Thomas Griffin &lt;thomas@thomasgriffinmedia.com&gt;&#10;@author Gary Jones &lt;gamajo@gamajo.com&gt;" ilk="class" line="1021" lineend="1592" name="TGMPA_List_Table"><scope attributes="public __ctor__" doc="References parent constructor and sets defaults for class.&#10;&#10;The constructor also grabs a copy of $instance from the TGMPA class&#10;and stores it in the global object TGM_Plugin_Activation::$instance.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;&#10;@global unknown $status&#10;@global string $page" ilk="function" line="1034" lineend="1046" name="__construct" signature="__construct()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="1036" name="page" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="1036" name="status" /></scope><scope attributes="protected" doc="Gathers and renames all of our plugin information to be used by&#10;WP_List_Table to create our table.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;&#10;@return array $table_data Information for use in table" ilk="function" line="1056" lineend="1155" name="_gather_plugin_data" returns="array" signature="array _gather_plugin_data()"><variable citdl="get_plugins()" line="1065" name="installed_plugins" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="1068" name="plugin" /><variable citdl="int" line="1064" name="i" /><variable citdl="array()" line="1063" name="table_data" /><variable citdl="array()" line="1133" name="req" /><variable citdl="array()" line="1132" name="resort" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="1141" name="type" /><variable citdl="add_query_arg()" line="1090" name="url" /><variable citdl="this._get_plugin_data_from_name()" line="1074" name="external_url" /><variable citdl="array()" line="1134" name="rec" /><variable citdl="this._get_plugin_data_from_name()" line="1075" name="source" /></scope><scope attributes="protected" doc="Retrieve plugin data, given the plugin name. Taken from the&#10;TGM_Plugin_Activation class.&#10;&#10;Loops through the registered plugins looking for $name. If it finds it,&#10;it returns the $data from that plugin. Otherwise, returns false.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;&#10;@param string $name Name of the plugin, as it was registered&#10;@param string $data Optional. Array key of plugin data to return. Default is slug&#10;@return string|boolean Plugin slug if found, false otherwise" ilk="function" line="1170" lineend="1179" name="_get_plugin_data_from_name" returns="string" signature="string _get_plugin_data_from_name(string $name, string $data = 'slug')"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="1170" name="name" /><variable citdl="string" default="'slug'" ilk="argument" line="1170" name="data" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="1173" name="values" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Create default columns to display important plugin information&#10;like type, action and status.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;&#10;@param array $item&#10;@param string $column_name" ilk="function" line="1190" lineend="1199" name="column_default" returns="item" signature="column_default(array $item, string $column_name)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="1190" name="item" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="1190" name="column_name" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Create default title column along with action links of 'Install'&#10;and 'Activate'.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;&#10;@param array $item&#10;@return string The action hover links" ilk="function" line="1210" lineend="1263" name="column_plugin" returns="string" signature="string column_plugin(array $item)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="1210" name="item" /><variable citdl="get_plugins()" line="1212" name="installed_plugins" /><variable citdl="array()" line="1215" name="actions" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Required for bulk installing.&#10;&#10;Adds a checkbox for each plugin.&#10;&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;&#10;@param array $item&#10;@return string The input checkbox with all necessary info" ilk="function" line="1275" lineend="1280" name="column_cb" returns="string" signature="string column_cb(array $item)"><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="1275" 